I paid 899 and ordered the kefir grains, received a small 30ml bottle filled with curd(not like image). I followed instructions and added milk, after 24 hrs I strained, found butter in strainer(image attached), dropped message and images on whatsapp to understand where are my Kefir grains. this guy highlighted something, I tried to feel the Kefir grains but it was just curd, Since then I am filling a glass bottle with room temperature milk and put strained so called "Kefir grains" and next day strain again, using glass jar, plastic bowl and plastic strainer as given in instructions, doing it from last 20 days but still not seen "kefir grains" like given in image. What i am feeling after 20 days. 1. Taste of this curd is far better then the packed curd available in market. 2. Repeating same process from last 20 days but did not see big like Kefir grains like in image 3. It taste very good like curd you get in small villages, there people don't buy curd from market but use last day curd again next day. 4. its definitely over prices since big kefir grains were not there. not happy with kefir grains i received, but taste was good
One person found this helpful
Feel good that I have discovered this great product which is value for money spent initially. I am getting the health benefits from consuming kefir on a daily basis. It’s been almost 5 months since I bought the grains and have managed to keep them alive and thriving. Follow the instructions given by Mr. Kefir and remember that being a helpful person he is always there to clear your doubts in case you may have any! Kefir is a hidden gem that most people have not discovered and it is the best way to consume probiotics in their natural form. Again I must say it is a great product available on Amazon so go ahead and buy without any doubts!
Looks Good & is Fine..Consumable having the effect needed...
I thought very long about this review. In some ways, I would have liked to give 5 stars; however, there are a few cons with the purchase. Overall, I would recommend going with this seller for kefir grains. Here are the pros and cons: Pros: —There is EXCELLENT customer service provided from the seller. Mr. Kefir is respectful and caring and truly wants to help make the process go smoothly for his customers. — The grains are covered by a one time 6 months no-questions-asked warranty —The grains are shipped in nice packaging with a spoon, strainer, personal note from the seller, and an instruction manual with contact information. —The grains produce kefir well, which is what the goal is, right!? Cons: — The price is very high for the size and amount of grains you get. —The tiny size of the grains makes straining/finding your grains a little challenging. —The strainer given is not good for straining kefir. It was very challenging to strain my kefir with the double mesh strainer, especially when the temperature was hot, producing very thick kefir so quickly. To solve this problem, I cut out one of the strainer layers with scissors, and the process became a thousand times easier! TAKE NOTE: Sometimes when people think their grains have multiplied/gotten bigger, it may just be kefir curds which have not yet gone through the strainer. This is especially true when using the double mesh strainer. Just because you have big lumps, does not mean you have bigger kefir grains. For those of you who may have a sourdough starter, kefir is similar (definitely not the same, but similar) in how it works with temperature. However, know that kefir grains are more sensitive to temperature changes, so they are not as forgiving as a sourdough starter when you forget to feed them or put them in the fridge. When the kefir grains grow larger, they can stand a little more change, but these baby grains have to be babied.
30 people found this helpful
The product came with clear instructions and everything you need to make your kefir curd. Mr. Kefir also gives you all the hand holding you may need to learn the process of setting your kefir curd. It's worth the money spent. And best of all I think it has already improved my digestion a good deal after consuming it daily for the last 15 days or so. So I would say, just go for it. Thanks.
Grains were well packed and reached within a day. I could also make a delicious Kefir with them. When the grains multiply so much and so easily, I think it is overly priced for no reason. The free strainer was of no use at all since the mesh has a very fine holes, that hardly filters out. Either give a workable strainer or pls do not give at all.
3 people found this helpful
I started using kefir grains about three weeks ago. I used it at first with whole cow's milk supplied by my neighbourhood dairy, and ran into a few issues because the fat was not evenly distributed in the milk. I sought support from Mr Kefir over the phone and on WhatsApp to overcome these teething problems. His response was simply superb, and he handheld me over the succeeding days to get properly set kefir. After this experience, I can say that the novice should start with pasteurized, homogenized milk. I have shown the packets of two brands that have worked well for me. The kefir is ready once the contents do not move when fermentation bottle is tilted. After straining, the kefir grains may be re-used to make another batch. The resulting kefir is tangy and tart and feels very good to eat. Highly recommended. Enjoy!
