 done my reading from various online sources on kefir. The culture received was a small quantity and I could only see small grains. The white liquid was very sour. However I followed the instructions by Mr. Kefir. Lo and behold, within two days we started making ~ 900 ml of kefir every day. We get chilled milk in packets delivered at home in the morning, and is immediately moved to refrigerator. The kefir grains are put in the glass jar (1 litre capacity) and topped up with ~ 900 ml of milk. The jar is not air tight. The jar is then placed in the refrigerator. We typically take the jar out of the refrigerator at around 8:00 PM, and keep the jar in the kitchen. The kefir is filtered at ~ 8:30 AM. During the last 4 months we had travelled a couple of weeks out of our residential town. No problems, keep the grains topped up with milk in the refrigerator till you come back from the travel. One thing I noticed is that the time required for making good kefir is weather dependent. In January, it took a little more time (typically out of the refrigerator at ~ 1:30 PM, peak day temperature in the range of 24C and night temperature of ~ 14C). Thank you Mr. Kefir! Anil 5.0 out of 5 stars I am successfully making high quality Kefir for the 4 months using the starter grains from Mr. Kefir Reviewed in India 🇮🇳 on 24 February 2023 I ordered the grains in October 2022. Before that I had done my reading from various online sources on kefir. The culture received was a small quantity and I could only see small grains. The white liquid was very sour. However I followed the instructions by Mr. Kefir. Lo and behold, within two days we started making ~ 900 ml of kefir every day. We get chilled milk in packets delivered at home in the morning, and is immediately moved to refrigerator. The kefir grains are put in the glass jar (1 litre capacity) and topped up with ~ 900 ml of milk. The jar is not air tight. The jar is then placed in the refrigerator. We typically take the jar out of the ref