It's been over a month since I started fermentation. Started as a fun project and got converted as a regular habbit now. Suggestions where we could go wrong: Do not use full fat buffalo milk. It will be very hard to strain as the kefir would be too thick to filter out. Use cow milk preferably, if you don't have the availablity then go for buffalo milk which is not full cream. I used amul milk pasterized
