The price is very high for the size and amount of grains you get. —The tiny size of the grains makes straining/finding your grains a little challenging. —The strainer given is not good for straining kefir. It was very challenging to strain my kefir with the double mesh strainer, especially when the temperature was hot, producing very thick kefir so quickly. To solve this problem, I cut out one of the strainer layers with scissors, and the process became a thousand times easier! TAKE NOTE: Sometimes when people think their grains have multiplied/gotten bigger, it may just be kefir curds which have not yet gone through the strainer. This is especially true when using the double mesh strainer. Just because you have big lumps, does not mean you have bigger kefir grains. For those of you who may have a sourdough starter, kefir is similar (definitely not the same, but similar) in how it works with temperature. However, know that kefir grains are more sensitive to temperature changes, so they are not as forgiving as a sourdough starter when you forget to feed them or put them in the fridge. When the kefir grains grow larger, they can stand a little more change, but these baby grains have to be babied. 30 people found this helpful Helpful Sending feedback...Thank you for your feedback.Sorry, we failed to record your vote. Please try again Report Showing 0 comments There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.Siddharth Verma5.0 out of 5 stars Effective and great service Reviewed in India 🇮🇳 on 29 July 2023Verified Purchase The product came with clear instructions and everything you need to make your kefir curd. Mr. Kefir also gives you all the hand holding you may need to learn the process of setting your kefir curd. It's worth the money spent. And best of all I think it has already improved my digestion a good deal after consuming it daily for the last 15 days or so. So I would say, just go for it. Thanks. Helpful Sending feedback...Thank you for y